Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and sprinkle with the @roasted spice and herb blend{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{250%g}, then cut it into 2cm chunks. Pop them into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{½}(peeled and sliced as thinly as possible).

Pop it into a small bowl with half the @red wine vinegar{24%ml} and the @sugar{1} for the pickle. Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together and set aside.

Cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 2cm chunks. Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}(trimmed and separated into bite-sized pieces), separate the leaves, then tear into bite-sized pieces.

Remove the halloumi chunks from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Wipe out the (now empty) halloumi bowl and pop in the @harissa paste{50%g} and @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Stir to combine, then set aside.

> Add less harissa paste if you'd prefer things milder.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, turning frequently, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once golden, remove the pan from the heat and allow to cool slightly.

While the halloumi fries, pop the @Greek style flatbreads{2} into the oven until warm, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, mix together the remaining red wine vinegar with the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and @sugar{½} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the chopped tomato and half the baby gem to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

When ready, pop a warm flatbread onto each #plate{}.

Spread over the harissa yoghurt sauce and scatter over the remaining lettuce. Top with the halloumi, then drizzle over the @fresh chilli jam{18.5%g}. Finish with as much pickled onion as you'd like.

Serve your halloumi gyros with the fries and tomato salad on the side. Enjoy!